main event: The shared document contains a range of UFO report forms from Project Blue Book. Witnesses reported seeing unidentified aerial objects, but many concluded that the sightings were likely aircraft or natural phenomena.
interesting points: The witnesses observed objects that appeared like shooting stars, changed brightness, and maneuvered in the sky for a brief duration.
The questionnaire includes detailed prompts for the observers to draw the shape and motion of the objects they saw.
The observed objects moved behind and in front of clouds, changing brightness and shape during the sightings.
The witnesses were asked to provide personal details, such as their location, the duration of the sighting, and educational background.
In one report, a civilian observer described seeing two sightings of one object appearing, getting larger, and then disappearing behind a cloud.
photographs: No photographs included in the report
